<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="173" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1566,1737]" pageId="1" pageNumber="173">
Auricle and evaporatorium of metathoracic scent gland as in 
<figureCitation box="[885,951,1602,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1714,1739]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,166,1694]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratype, SEM micrographs. a, metathoracic scent gland; b, suture between meso- and metapleura; c, sternites IV–V; d, anterior trichobothria on sternite V; e, tibial comb; f, hind claw complex. Arrows indicate spiracles." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673407/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="173">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
a–b. Detailed structure of trichobothria and associated abdominal sternites IV and V as in 
<figureCitation box="[671,736,1638,1664]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1714,1739]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,166,1694]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratype, SEM micrographs. a, metathoracic scent gland; b, suture between meso- and metapleura; c, sternites IV–V; d, anterior trichobothria on sternite V; e, tibial comb; f, hind claw complex. Arrows indicate spiracles." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673407/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="173">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
c–d. Bothrium not sunken below surface of the cuticle and trichomes present, with uniform spine-like microtrichia, which belong to the most common 
<typeStatus box="[1171,1219,1675,1701]" pageId="1" pageNumber="173">type</typeStatus>
within Lygaeoidea (
<bibRefCitation author="Gao, C. Q. &amp; Redei, D. &amp; Shi, X. Q. &amp; Cai, B. &amp; Liang, K. &amp; Gao, S. &amp; Bu, W. J." box="[159,338,1710,1736]" pageId="1" pageNumber="173" pagination="587 - 602" refId="ref4515" refString="Gao, C. Q., Redei, D., Shi, X. Q., Cai, B., Liang, K., Gao, S. &amp; Bu, W. J. (2017) A comparative study of the abdominal trichobothria of Trichophora, with emphasis on Lygaeoidea (Hemiptera: Heteroptera). European Journal of Entomology, 114, 587 - 602. https: // doi. org / 10.14411 / eje. 2017.072" type="journal article" year="2017">
Gao 
<emphasis box="[214,270,1710,1736]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="173">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). Tibial comb of fore leg and claw complex as in 
<figureCitation box="[892,956,1710,1736]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1714,1739]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,166,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,166,1694]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Meschia zoui sp. nov. paratype, SEM micrographs. a, metathoracic scent gland; b, suture between meso- and metapleura; c, sternites IV–V; d, anterior trichobothria on sternite V; e, tibial comb; f, hind claw complex. Arrows indicate spiracles." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2673407/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="173">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
e–f.
</paragraph>
